# API Conventions

## Response Envelope

Every endpoint wraps its response:

```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean;
  data: T;
  error?: { code: string; message: string };
}
```

Never return a raw object or array at the top level.

## Error Codes — Stable, Switchable

The mobile app `switch`es on `code` — never make the client parse error strings.

```typescript
// BAD — mobile must parse the message string
throw new BadRequestException('The slot is already taken');

// GOOD — stable machine-readable code
throw new ConflictException({ code: 'BOOKING_SLOT_TAKEN', message: 'This slot is already booked' });
```

## Pagination

- Feeds and lists: cursor-based (`nextCursor` token) preferred.
- Admin/dashboard: offset acceptable.
- **Never return unbounded arrays.** Every list endpoint enforces a `limit`.

## Timestamps

All timestamps ISO 8601 UTC: `2025-01-15T10:30:00.000Z`. Let the client handle timezone display.

## GeoJSON — Critical Field Order

`[longitude, latitude]` — NOT `[lat, lng]`. Wrong order causes silent geo query failures.

```typescript
// BAD — reversed coordinates
location: { type: 'Point', coordinates: [latitude, longitude] }

// GOOD — GeoJSON standard
location: { type: 'Point', coordinates: [longitude, latitude] }
```

Double-check every geo field added.

## File Uploads

Go through signed URLs (S3/Cloudinary pattern). Never accept raw multipart bodies into the NestJS process for anything beyond small avatars.

## Sync-Heavy Endpoints

Bookings and provider availability endpoints MUST support `updatedAfter` query param or `If-Modified-Since`/ETags for incremental mobile fetches — avoid full reloads.

## Push Notification Payloads

Define a typed interface per notification type. No ad-hoc string templates scattered across services.

```typescript
// BAD
notify(userId, `Your booking at ${time} is confirmed`);

// GOOD
interface BookingConfirmedPayload {
  type: 'BOOKING_CONFIRMED';
  bookingId: string;
  providerName: string;
  scheduledAt: string;
}
notify<BookingConfirmedPayload>(userId, { type: 'BOOKING_CONFIRMED', bookingId, providerName, scheduledAt });
```
